medical_history.chief_complaint: Headache and visual symptoms in a pregnant woman.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 2 weeks prior to admission with neck pain. Eleven days before admission, she experienced neck and back pain, occipital headache, vomiting, and a recorded fever of 38.9Â°C. On the day of presentation, she had a panic attack with tunnel vision, followed by blacking out from the periphery of her vision, which lasted about 2 minutes, leading to persistent headache, neck pain radiating to her arms, nausea, and dizziness.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Past medical history includes anemia due to iron deficiency, bipolar disorder, panic attacks, recurrent pelvic pain with pelvic adhesions, benign ovarian cysts, asthma, seasonal allergic rhinitis, and a previous female stillbirth at 20 weeks due to sepsis. She has undergone multiple laparoscopies, including cholecystectomy and ovarian cystectomies.
medical_history.family_history: Her mother had breast cancer and died in her 50s.
medical_history.social_history: Patient does not smoke, drink alcohol, or use illicit drugs. She lives with her boyfriend and was on disability benefits due to bipolar disorder. Born in Guatemala, she immigrated to the U.S. 15 years ago and last visited Guatemala 3 years ago.
